# Language Rules for Iconik Project

## UI Text (Spanish)
- All text visible to users in the interface must be in Spanish
- This includes:
  - Button labels
  - Form labels and placeholders
  - Navigation menu items
  - Error messages
  - Success notifications
  - Modal titles and content
  - Page headers and descriptions
  - Table headers and data labels
  - Tooltips and help text

## Code and Comments (English)
- All code, including:
  - Variable names
  - Function names
  - Class names
  - File names
  - API endpoints
  - Database field names
  - Configuration keys
- All comments in code must be in English
- Documentation and README files should be in English

## Examples
✅ Correct:
- UI: "Crear Cita", "Guardar Cambios", "Error al cargar datos"
- Code: `createAppointment()`, `saveChanges()`, `handleDataLoadError()`
- Comments: `// Handle user authentication`, `/* Process payment data */`

❌ Incorrect:
- UI: "Create Appointment", "Save Changes", "Error loading data"
- Code: `crearCita()`, `guardarCambios()`, `manejarErrorCargaDatos()`
- Comments: `// Manejar autenticación de usuario`, `/* Procesar datos de pago */`





